[normal]              
[normal]Gregory Barker:[bold] ECO is an incentive; it is a direct subsidy.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Q213[bold] 
[normal]Dr Whitehead:[bold] Yes. The inclusion of heat networks into qualifying measures for ECO purposes under the latest measures announced by the Department is welcome, in principle, but my point 
[normal]is in terms of the EU ETS, the Renewable Heat Incentive, the 
[normal]Renewables
[normal] O
[normal]bligation and CFDs for the future. CHP and heat networks simply do not come into that picture, do they?
[normal]              
